trend_summary: From earliest frame to latest, the eastern corridor shifts from bare earth to a continuous band of warehouses and offices, while the residential grid remains largely unchanged. Scattered infill and larger commercial roofs slightly raise overall coverage. Transport corridor widens, new parking lots appear, and tree cover modestly increases in western parks.
notable_changes: Cleared parcel in the northeast redeveloped into a multi-building warehouse/office complex.
Additional light-industrial sheds infilled along the rail/highway spine.
North-south transport corridor broadened with new overpass or ramp infrastructure.
Vacant lots converted to parking areas and sports fields near the center-south.
Gradual increase in street and park tree canopy, especially in the western sector.
